tion that led him to the pyre.This concise, compelling, and original reflection on the systems of (in)justice in seventeenth-century Mexico is designed for classes on early modern Spain, colonial Latin America, and the Inquisition. Those with an affinity for Irish history will also enjoy learning about the colorful life of William Lamport.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh1 aHeifetz, Hank.1 aRestall, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074510840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978027109200340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271092003423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271092003/original  a978-3-11-074510-8  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK